    }
    stopTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
    this.runningState = STATE_STOPPED;
}
```

### Issues in the Buggy Function
1. The condition checks if the `runningState` is neither `STATE_RUNNING` nor `STATE_SUSPENDED`. This means that if the stopwatch is either stopped or initialized, it will throw an exception. This might not be the intended behavior.
